Label: head of government
Description: head of the executive power of this town, city, municipality, state, country, or other governmental body

Label: video
Description: relevant video. For images, use the property P18. For film trailers, qualify with "object has role" (P3831)="trailer" (Q622550)

Label: traffic sign
Description: graphic symbol describing the item, used at the side of or above roads to give instructions or provide information to road users

Label: route map
Description: image of route map at Wikimedia Commons

Label: transport network
Description: network the infrastructure is a part of

Label: country
Description: sovereign state that this item is in (not to be used for human beings)

Label: image
Description: image of relevant illustration of the subject; if available, also use more specific properties (sample: coat of arms image, locator map, flag image, signature image, logo image, collage image)

Label: place of birth
Description: most specific known birth location of a person, animal or fictional character

Label: place of death
Description: most specific known (e.g. city instead of country, or hospital instead of city) death location of a person, animal or fictional character

Label: sex or gender
Description: sex or gender identity of human or animal. For human: male, female, non-binary, intersex, transgender female, transgender male, agender, etc. For animal: male organism, female organism. Groups of same gender use subclass of (P279)

Label: father
Description: male parent of the subject. For stepfather, use "stepparent" (P3448)

Label: mother
Description: female parent of the subject. For stepmother, use "stepparent" (P3448)

Label: spouse
Description: the subject has the object as their spouse (husband, wife, partner, etc.). Use "unmarried partner" (P451) for non-married companions

Label: country of citizenship
Description: the object is a country that recognizes the subject as its citizen

Label: continent
Description: continent of which the subject is a part

Label: instance of
Description: that class of which this subject is a particular example and member; different from P279 (subclass of); for example: K2 is an instance of mountain; volcano is a subclass of mountain (and an instance of volcanic landform)

Label: head of state
Description: official with the highest formal authority in a country/state

Label: capital
Description: seat of government of a country, province, state or other type of administrative territorial entity

Label: official language
Description: language designated as official by this item

Label: currency
Description: currency used by item

Label: position held
Description: subject currently or formerly holds the object position or public office

Label: child
Description: subject has object as child. Do not use for stepchildren—use "relative" (P1038), qualified with "type of kinship" (P1039)

Label: flag image
Description: image of the item's flag

Label: shares border with
Description: countries or administrative subdivisions, of equal level, that this item borders, either by land or water. A single common point is enough.

Label: author
Description: main creator(s) of a written work (use on works, not humans); use P2093 (author name string) when Wikidata item is unknown or does not exist

Label: audio
Description: relevant sound. If available, use a more specific property. Samples: "spoken text audio" (P989), "pronunciation audio" (P443)

Label: family
Description: family, including dynasty and nobility houses. Not family name (use P734 for family name).

Label: member of sports team
Description: sports teams or clubs that the subject represents or represented

Label: director
Description: director(s) of film, TV-series, stageplay, video game or similar

Label: screenwriter
Description: person(s) who wrote the script for subject item

Label: constellation
Description: the area of the celestial sphere of which the subject is a part (from a scientific standpoint, not an astrological one)

Label: discoverer or inventor
Description: subject who discovered, first described, invented, or developed this discovery or invention or scientific hypothesis or theory

Label: site of astronomical discovery
Description: the place where an astronomical object was discovered (observatory, satellite)

Label: ancestral home
Description: place of origin for ancestors of subject

Label: educated at
Description: educational institution attended by subject

Label: top-level Internet domain
Description: Internet domain name system top-level code

Label: connecting line
Description: railway line(s) subject is directly connected to

Label: architect
Description: person or architectural firm responsible for designing this building

Label: anthem
Description: subject's official anthem

Label: composer
Description: person(s) who wrote the music [for lyricist, use "lyrics by" (P676)]

Label: librettist
Description: author of the libretto (words) of an opera, operetta, oratorio or cantata, or of the book of a musical

Label: commissioned by
Description: person or organization that commissioned this work

Label: sexual orientation
Description: the sexual orientation of the person relative to their declared gender — use ONLY IF they have stated it themselves, unambiguously, or it has been widely agreed upon by historians after their death

Label: main regulatory text
Description: text setting the main rules by which the subject is regulated

Label: coat of arms image
Description: image of the item's coat of arms - for the shield part only use P4004

Label: noble title
Description: titles held by the person

Label: editor
Description: person who checks and corrects a work (such as a book, newspaper, academic journal, etc.) to comply with a rules of certain genre. Also applies to person who establishes the text of an ancient written work or manuscript.

Label: field of work
Description: specialization of a person or organization; see P106 for the occupation

Label: member of political party
Description: the political party of which a person is or has been a member or otherwise affiliated

Label: native language
Description: language or languages a person has learned from early childhood

Label: taxon rank
Description: level in a taxonomic hierarchy

Label: occupation
Description: occupation of a person; see also "field of work" (Property:P101), "position held" (Property:P39)

Label: employer
Description: person or organization for which the subject works or worked

Label: signature
Description: image of a person's signature

Label: illustrator
Description: person drawing the pictures or taking the photographs in a book or similar work

Label: measured physical quantity
Description: value of a physical property expressed as number multiplied by a unit

Label: founded by
Description: founder or co-founder of this organization, religion, place or entity

Label: airline hub
Description: airport that serves as a hub for an airline

Label: airline alliance
Description: alliance the airline belongs to

Label: home venue
Description: home stadium or venue of a sports team or applicable performing arts organization

Label: chemical structure
Description: image of a representation of the structure for a chemical compound

Label: league or competition
Description: league or competition in which team or player has played, or in which an event occurs

Label: place of burial
Description: location of grave, resting place, place of ash-scattering, etc. (e.g., town/city or cemetery) for a person or animal. There may be several places: e.g., re-burials, parts of body buried separately.

Label: item operated
Description: equipment, installation or service operated by the subject

Label: basic form of government
Description: subject's government

Label: publisher
Description: organization or person responsible for publishing books, periodicals, printed music, podcasts, games or software

Label: maintained by
Description: person or organization in charge of keeping the subject (for instance an infrastructure) in functioning order

Label: owned by
Description: owner of the subject

Label: regulates (molecular biology)
Description: process regulated by a protein or RNA in molecular biology

Label: physically interacts with
Description: physical entity that the subject interacts with

Label: located in the administrative territorial entity
Description: the item is located on the territory of the following administrative entity. Use P276 for specifying locations that are non-administrative places and for items about events. Use P1382 if the item falls only partially into the administrative entity.

Label: movement
Description: literary, artistic, scientific or philosophical movement or scene associated with this person or work. For political ideologies use P1142.

Label: genre
Description: creative work's genre or an artist's field of work (P101). Use main subject (P921) to relate creative works to their topic

Label: operator
Description: person, profession, organization or entity that operates the equipment, facility, or service

Label: named after
Description: entity or event that inspired the subject's name, or namesake (in at least one language). Qualifier "applies to name" (P5168) can be used to indicate which one

Label: religion or worldview
Description: religion of a person, organization or religious building, or associated with this subject

Label: IUCN conservation status
Description: conservation status assigned by the International Union for Conservation of Nature

Label: imported from Wikimedia project
Description: source of this claim's value; used in references section by bots or humans importing data from Wikimedia projects

Label: based on
Description: the work(s) or inputs used as the basis for subject item; for fictional analog use P1074

Label: architectural style
Description: architectural style of a structure

Label: contains the administrative territorial entity
Description: (list of) direct subdivisions of an administrative territorial entity

Label: logo image
Description: graphic mark or emblem commonly used by commercial enterprises, organizations and products

Label: follows
Description: immediately prior item in a series of which the subject is a part, preferably use as qualifier of P179 [if the subject has replaced the preceding item, e.g. political offices, use "replaces" (P1365)]

Label: followed by
Description: immediately following item in a series of which the subject is a part, preferably use as qualifier of P179 [if the subject has been replaced, e.g. political offices, use "replaced by" (P1366)]

Label: killed by
Description: person or organization who killed the subject

Label: seal image
Description: image of subject's seal (emblem)

Label: headquarters location
Description: city or town where an organization's headquarters is or has been situated. Use P276 qualifier for specific building

Label: cast member
Description: actor in the subject production [use "character role" (P453) and/or "name of the character role" (P4633) as qualifiers] [use "voice actor" (P725) for voice-only role] - [use "recorded participant" (P11108) for non-fiction productions]

Label: producer
Description: person(s) who produced the film, musical work, theatrical production, etc. (for film, this does not include executive producers, associate producers, etc.) [for production company, use P272, video games - use P178]

Label: flag
Description: subject's flag

Label: award received
Description: award or recognition received by a person, organization or creative work

Label: structure replaced by
Description: the item which replaced this building or structure, at the same geographic location

Label: chief executive officer
Description: highest-ranking corporate officer appointed as the CEO within an organization

Label: creator
Description: maker of this creative work or other object (where no more specific property exists)

Label: parent taxon
Description: closest parent taxon of the taxon in question

Label: ethnic group
Description: subject's ethnicity (consensus is that a VERY high standard of proof is needed for this field to be used. In general this means 1) the subject claims it themselves, or 2) it is widely agreed on by scholars, or 3) is fictional and portrayed as such)

Label: performer
Description: actor, musician, band or other performer associated with this role or musical work

Label: manufacturer
Description: (main or final) manufacturer or producer of this product

Label: crosses
Description: obstacle (body of water, road, railway...) which this bridge (ferry, ford) crosses over or this tunnel goes under

Label: developer
Description: organization or person that developed the item

Label: part of the series
Description: series which contains the subject

Label: depicts
Description: entity visually depicted in an image, literarily described in a work, or otherwise incorporated into an audiovisual or other medium; see also P921,  'main subject'

Label: taxon range map image
Description: range map of a taxon

Label: endemic to
Description: sole location or habitat type where the taxon lives

Label: doctoral advisor
Description: person who supervised the doctorate or PhD thesis of the subject

Label: doctoral student
Description: doctoral student(s) of a professor

Label: made from material
Description: material the subject or the object is made of or derived from (do not confuse with P10672 which is used for processes)

Label: location of discovery
Description: where the item was located when discovered

Label: twinned administrative body
Description: twin towns, sister cities, twinned municipalities and other localities that have a partnership or cooperative agreement, either legally or informally acknowledged by their governments

Label: main building contractor
Description: the main organization (or person) responsible for construction of this structure or building

Label: legislative body
Description: legislative body governing this entity; political institution with elected representatives, such as a parliament/legislature or council

Label: collection
Description: art, museum, archival, or bibliographic collection of which the subject is part

Label: minor planet group
Description: is in grouping of minor planets according to similar orbital characteristics

Label: adjacent station
Description: the stations next to this station, sharing the same line(s)

Label: organizational divisions
Description: organizational divisions of this organization (which are not independent legal entities)

Label: inflows
Description: major inflow sources — rivers, aquifers, glacial runoff, etc. Some terms may not be place names, e.g. none

Label: outflows
Description: rivers and other outflows waterway names. If evaporation or seepage are notable outflows, they may be included. Some terms may not be place names, e.g. evaporation

Label: basin country
Description: country that have drainage to/from or border the body of water

Label: located in or next to body of water
Description: body of water on or next to which a place is located

Label: bathymetry image
Description: image showing bathymetric chart, bathymetric map

Label: executive body
Description: branch of government for the daily administration of the territorial entity

Label: highest judicial authority
Description: supreme judicial body within a country, administrative division, or other organization

Label: party chief representative
Description: chief representative of a party in an institution or an administrative unit (use qualifier to identify the party)

Label: ISBN-13
Description: identifier for a book (edition), thirteen digit

Label: ISNI
Description: International Standard Name Identifier for an identity. Starting with 0000.

Label: VIAF cluster ID
Description: identifier for the Virtual International Authority File database [format: up to 22 digits]; please note: VIAF is a cluster, the ID can include multiple items

Label: spectral class
Description: spectral class of an astronomical object

Label: inventory number
Description: identifier for a physical object or a set of physical objects in a collection

Label: ISO 639-1 code
Description: 2-letter identifier for language or family of languages defined in ISO 639-1 standard

Label: ISO 639-2 code
Description: 3-letter identifier for language,  macro-language or language family, defined in ISO 639-2 standard

Label: ISO 639-3 code
Description: 3-letter identifier for language defined in ISO 639-3, extension of ISO 639-2

Label: ISO 639-6 code
Description: 4-letter identifier for language variants per ISO 639-6, standard between 2009-2014

Label: galaxy morphological type
Description: galaxy morphological classification code

Label: taxon name
Description: correct scientific name of a taxon (according to the reference given)

Label: GND ID
Description: identifier from an international authority file of names, subjects, and organizations

Label: IATA airline designator
Description: two-character identifier for an airline

Label: ICAO airline designator
Description: three letter identifier for an airline (two letters only until 1982) (for airports, see P239)

Label: CAS Registry Number
Description: identifier for a chemical substance or compound per Chemical Abstract Service's Registry database

Label: EC number
Description: identifier for a chemical compound per EINECS or ELINCS

Label: canonical SMILES
Description: Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry Specification (canonical format)

Label: InChI
Description: International Chemical Identifier

Label: InChIKey
Description: a hashed version of the full standard InChI

Label: ISSN
Description: International Standard Serial Number (print or electronic)

Label: coat of arms
Description: subject's coat of arms

Label: IATA airport code
Description: three-letter identifier for designating airports, railway stations or cities (for airlines, see P229)

Label: ICAO airport code
Description: four-character alphanumeric identifier for designating airports (for airlines, see P230)

Label: FAA airport code
Description: three-letter or four-letter alphanumeric code identifying United States airports

Label: military branch
Description: branch to which this military unit, award, office, or person belongs, e.g. Royal Navy

Label: locator map image
Description: geographic map image which highlights the location of the subject within some larger entity

Label: OCLC control number
Description: identifier for a bibliographic record in OCLC WorldCat

Label: Library of Congress authority ID
Description: Library of Congress name authority (persons, families, corporate bodies, events, places, works and expressions) and subject authority identifier [Format: 1-2 specific letters followed by 8-10 digits (see regex). For manifestations, use P1144]

Label: Union List of Artist Names ID
Description: identifier from the Getty Union List of Artist Names

Label: element symbol
Description: identifier for a chemical element

Label: COSPAR ID
Description: international satellite designation, administered by the UN Committee on Space Research (COSPAR), similar but not synonymous with the NSSDCA ID (P8913)

Label: stated in
Description: to be used in the references field to refer to the information document or database in which a claim is made; for qualifiers use P805; for the type of document in which a claim is made use P3865

Label: ticker symbol
Description: identifier for a publicly traded share of a particular stock on a particular stock market or that of a cryptocurrency (qualifier for P414)

Label: official residence
Description: the residence at which heads of government and other senior figures officially reside

Label: record label
Description: brand and trademark associated with the marketing of subject music recordings and music videos

Label: ATC code
Description: therapeutic chemical identification code per ATC

Label: Bibliothèque nationale de France ID
Description: identifier for the subject issued by BNF (Bibliothèque nationale de France). Format: 8 digits followed by a check-digit or letter, do not include the initial 'cb'.

Label: IdRef ID
Description: identifier for authority control in the French collaborative library catalog (see also P1025). Format: 8 digits followed by a digit or "X"

Label: CALIS ID
Description: identifier for authority control per CALIS (China Academic Library & Information System)

Label: NACSIS-CAT author ID
Description: identifier for book authors in NACSIS-CAT, the union catalog for university libraries and research institutions in Japan

Label: production company
Description: company that produced this film, audio or performing arts work

Label: chemical formula
Description: description of chemical compound giving element symbols and counts

Label: copyright license
Description: license under which this copyrighted work is released

Label: location
Description: location of the object, structure or event. In the case of an administrative entity as containing item use P131. For statistical entities use P8138. In the case of a geographic entity use P706. Use P7153 for locations associated with the object

Label: programmed in
Description: the programming language(s) in which the software is developed

Label: GOST 7.75–97 code
Description: identifier for a language according to GOST 7.75–97

Label: subclass of
Description: this item is a subclass (subset) of that item; all instances of this item are instances of that item; different from P31 (instance of), e.g.: volcano is a subclass of mountain (and an instance of volcanic landform); Everest is an instance of mountain

Label: postal code
Description: identifier assigned by postal authorities for the subject area or building

Label: writing system
Description: alphabet, character set or other system of writing used by a language, word, or text, supported by a typeface

Label: head coach
Description: on-field manager or head coach of a sports club (not to be confused with a general manager P505, which is not a coaching position) or person

Label: designed by
Description: person or organization which designed the object

Label: vessel class
Description: series of vessels or other watercraft built to the same design of which this vessel is a member

Label: place of publication
Description: geographical place of publication of the edition (use 1st edition when referring to works)

Label: station code
Description: generic identifier for a railway station, when possible, use specific property on certain coding system (e.g. P1378 for China Railway TMIS codes)

Label: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code
Description: identifier for a country in two-letter format per ISO 3166-1

Label: ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 code
Description: identifier for a country in three-letter format per ISO 3166-1

Label: ISO 3166-1 numeric code
Description: identifier for a country in numeric format per ISO 3166-1

Label: ISO 3166-2 code
Description: identifier for a country subdivision per ISO 3166-2 (include country code)

Label: category's main topic
Description: primary topic of the subject Wikimedia category

Label: EE breed number
Description: breed identification number per the EE list of the breeds of fancy pigeons (ELFP)

Label: page(s)
Description: page number of source referenced for statement. Note "column(s)" (P3903) and "folio(s)" (P7416) for other numbering systems

Label: IETF language tag
Description: identifier for language or languoid per the Internet Engineering Task Force; can include a primary language subtag, subtags for script, region, variant, extension, or private-use. Format: 2 or 3 letters, followed by "-" if subtags present

Label: operating system
Description: operating system (OS) on which a software works or the OS installed on hardware

Label: director of photography
Description: person responsible for the framing, lighting, and filtration of the subject work

Label: IMDb ID
Description: identifier for the IMDb (with prefix 'tt', 'nm', 'co', 'ev', 'ch' or 'ni')

Label: Joconde work ID
Description: identifier in the Joconde database of the French Ministry of Culture

Label: software version identifier
Description: numeric or nominal identifier of a version of a software program or file format, current or past

Label: NDL Authority ID
Description: identifier for authority control per the National Diet Library of Japan

Label: RKDimages ID
Description: identifier per RKDimages of the Netherlands Institute for Art History

Label: Entrez Gene ID
Description: identifier for a gene per the NCBI Entrez database

Label: UniProt protein ID
Description: identifier for a protein per the UniProt database

Label: HGNC gene symbol
Description: the official gene symbol approved by the HGNC, which is typically a short form of the gene name

Label: HGNC ID
Description: a unique ID provided by the HGNC for each gene with an approved symbol. HGNC IDs remain stable even if a name or symbol changes

Label: has subsidiary
Description: subsidiary of a company or organization; generally a fully owned separate corporation. Compare with "business division" (P199). Opposite of parent organization (P749).

Label: DOI
Description: serial code used to uniquely identify digital objects like academic papers (use upper case letters only)

Label: discography
Description: item for list pages with discography of artist or band

Label: Rijksmonument ID
Description: identifier for a monument assigned by the Rijksdienst voor het Cultureel Erfgoed

Label: is a list of
Description: common element between all listed items

Label: part of
Description: object of which the subject is a part (if this subject is already part of object A which is a part of object B, then please only make the subject part of object A), inverse property of "has part" (P527, see also "has parts of the class" (P2670))

Label: original language of film or TV show
Description: language in which a film or a performance work was originally created. Deprecated for written works and songs; use P407 ("language of work or name") instead.

Label: has use
Description: main use of the subject (includes current and former usage)

Label: astronomic symbol image
Description: image of the symbol that identify a planet or an asteroid of the solar system

Label: Sandbox-CommonsMediaFile
Description: Sandbox property for value of type "Commons Media File"

Label: Sandbox-Item
Description: Sandbox property for value of type "Item"

Label: Sandbox-String
Description: Sandbox property for the data value type "String"

Label: presenter
Description: main role in presenting a radio or television program or a performing arts show

Label: Commons category
Description: name of the Wikimedia Commons category containing files related to this item (without the prefix "Category:")

Label: INSEE municipality code
Description: identifier with 5 digits or letters for a municipality or a municipal arrondissement in France, per the National Institute of Statistics and Economic Studies

Label: space launch vehicle
Description: type of rocket or other vehicle for launching subject payload into outer space

Label: located on astronomical body
Description: single astronomical body on which features or places are situated

Label: SCN
Description: Satellite Catalog Number, 5-digit-number including leading zeros (e.g. '00266')

Label: Mérimée ID
Description: identifier for a monument in the Mérimée database of French cultural heritage

Label: PCP reference number
Description: identifier for cultural properties in Switzerland

Label: CBS municipality code
Description: identifier for a Dutch municipality as defined by Statistics Netherlands (CBS)

Label: edition number
Description: number of an edition (first, second, ... as 1, 2, ...) or event

Label: licence plate code
Description: distinguishing signs or parts of license plate associated with the subject. For countries: international licence plate country code or distinguishing sign of vehicles

Label: SBN author ID
Description: identifier issued by National Library Service (SBN) of Italy

Label: parent astronomical body
Description: major astronomical body the item belongs to

Label: child astronomical body
Description: minor body that belongs to the item

Label: companion of
Description: two or more astronomic bodies of the same type relating to each other

Label: platform
Description: platform for which a work was developed or released, or the specific platform version of a software product

Label: OpenStreetMap relation ID
Description: identifier for a relation in OpenStreetMap

Label: mouth of the watercourse
Description: the body of water to which the watercourse drains

Label: game mode
Description: video game's available playing mode(s)

Label: taxon author
Description: the author(s) that (optionally) may be cited with the scientific name

Label: soundtrack release
Description: music release that incorporates music directly recorded from the soundtrack of an audiovisual work

Label: language of work or name
Description: language associated with this creative work (such as books, shows, songs, broadcasts or websites) or a name (for persons use "native language" (P103) and "languages spoken, written or signed" (P1412))

Label: software engine
Description: software engine employed by the subject item

Label: Libraries Australia ID
Description: identifier issued by the National Library of Australia (see also P1315 for the newer People Australia identifier). VIAF component. Format: 1-12 digits, removing leading zero-padding.

Label: military or police rank
Description: military or police rank achieved by a person (should usually have a "start time" qualifier), or military or police rank associated with a position

Label: canonization status
Description: formal stage in the process of attaining sainthood per the subject's religious organization

Label: voice type
Description: person's voice type. expected values: soprano, mezzo-soprano, contralto, countertenor, tenor, baritone, bass (and derivatives)

Label: position played on team / speciality
Description: position or specialism of a player on a team

Label: stock exchange
Description: exchange on which this company is traded

Label: radio format
Description: describes the overall content broadcast on a radio station

Label: quantity symbol (string)
Description: symbol for a mathematical or physical quantity

Label: patron saint
Description: patron saint adopted by the subject

Label: has seal, badge, or sigil
Description: links to the item for the subject's seal

Label: located in time zone
Description: time zone for this item

Label: shooting handedness
Description: whether the hockey player passes or shoots left- or right-handed

Label: Wikimedia language code
Description: identifier for a language or variant as used by Wikimedia projects

Label: field of this occupation
Description: field corresponding to this occupation or profession (use only for occupations/professions - for people use Property:P101, for companies use P452)

Label: aircraft registration
Description: identifier assigned to an individual aircraft by civil aircraft registry

Label: taxonomic type
Description: type genus or species: [in zoology:] nominal genus or species that is the name-bearing type of this nominal family or genus (or family-group ranked taxon or subgenus); type specimen that is the name-bearing type of this nominal species or subspecies

Label: botanist author abbreviation
Description: standard form (official abbreviation) of a personal name for use in an author citation (only for names of algae, fungi and plants)

Label: dantai code
Description: identifier for administrative division in 6-digit format assigned by the interior ministry of Japan

Label: callsign of airline
Description: identifier used in radio transmissions to refer to the subject airline

Label: issue
Description: issue of a newspaper, a scientific journal or magazine for reference purpose

Label: MusicBrainz artist ID
Description: identifier for an artist in the MusicBrainz open music encyclopedia

Label: MusicBrainz work ID
Description: identifier for a work per the MusicBrainz open music encyclopedia

Label: MusicBrainz release group ID
Description: identifier for a release group per the MusicBrainz open music encyclopedia (album, single, etc.)

Label: distribution format
Description: method (or type) of distribution for the subject

Label: German municipality key
Description: identifier for municipalities and independent towns in Germany

Label: German district key
Description: identifier for districts (Landkreise) and independent towns in Germany

Label: China administrative division code
Description: identifier for administrative divisions of People's Republic of China (with spaces)

Label: pronunciation audio
Description: audio file with pronunciation

Label: review score
Description: review score received by a creative work or other entity

Label: review score by
Description: issuer of a review score

Label: original broadcaster
Description: network(s) or service(s) that originally broadcast a radio or television program

Label: astronaut mission
Description: space mission that the subject is or has been a member of (do not include future missions)

Label: unmarried partner
Description: someone with whom the person is in a relationship without being married. Use "spouse" (P26) for married couples

Label: industry
Description: specific industry of company or organization

Label: character role
Description: specific role played or filled by subject -- use only as qualifier of "cast member" (P161), "voice actor" (P725)

Label: Structurae structure ID
Description: identifier for a building in the Structurae database

Label: Emporis building ID
Description: former identifier for a building in the defunct Emporis database (for building complexes, see P2270)

Label: foundational text
Description: text through which an institution or object has been created or established

Label: IMO ship number
Description: identifier for a ship, ship owner or ship manager per the International Maritime Organization

Label: determination method or standard
Description: how a value is determined, or the standard by which it is declared

Label: said to be the same as
Description: this item is said to be the same as that item, though this may be uncertain or disputed

Label: opposite of
Description: item that is in some way the opposite of this item

Label: color
Description: color of subject

Label: member of
Description: organization, club or musical group to which the subject belongs. Do not use for membership in ethnic or social groups, nor for holding a political position, such as a member of parliament (use P39 for that)

Label: NOR numbering ID
Description: identifier for French official texts

Label: sRGB color hex triplet
Description: sRGB hex triplet format for subject color (e.g. 7FFFD4) specifying the 8-bit red, green and blue components

Label: occupant
Description: person or organization occupying property

Label: legislated by
